      • getKmlColor

        public java.lang.String getKmlColor​(java.lang.String hexColor,
                                    @Nullable
                                    java.lang.Integer opacity)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Converts standard HEX color from HTML User input into KML color standard. ==================================================================== https://developers.google.com/kml/documentation/kmlreference#colorstyle Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. The order of expression is aabbggrr, where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.

        * Typical RGB incoming from HTML color picker list (as #rrggbb): * HEX COLOR : #ff0000 * HEX COLOR : #000000 * HEX COLOR : #ffffff * HEX COLOR : #8e4848

        Parameters:
        hexColor - "#rrggbb" (reg, green, blue) natural input from HTML color picker in hex MultipartDto#getPointTextHexColor() or MultipartDto#getPointTextHexColorDynamic()
        opacity - Percentage value from 0 to 100%. MultipartDto#getPointTextOpacity() or MultipartDto#getPointTextOpacityDynamic() If null, the max "ff" value will be set.
        Returns:
        kml specific color with opacity (alpha-channel) as "aabbggrr" (alpha, blue, green,red) witch is corresponds to KML specification.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException

        public java.lang.String getKmlColor​(java.lang.String hexColor,

        Converts standard HEX color from HTML User input into KML color standard. ==================================================================== https://developers.google.com/kml/documentation/kmlreference#colorstyle Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. The order of expression is aabbggrr, where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.

        * Typical RGB incoming from HTML color picker list (as #rrggbb): * HEX COLOR : #ff0000 * HEX COLOR : #000000 * HEX COLOR : #ffffff * HEX COLOR : #8e4848

        Parameters:
        hexColor - "#rrggbb" (reg, green, blue) natural input from HTML color picker in hex MultipartDto#getPointTextHexColor() or MultipartDto#getPointTextHexColorDynamic()
        hexOpacity - Hexadecimal value from 00 to FF. MultipartDto.getPointTextHexOpacity() or MultipartDto.getPointTextHexOpacityDynamic() If null, the max "ff" value will be set.
        Returns:

      • getHexFromPercentage

        java.lang.String getHexFromPercentage​(java.lang.Integer percentage)
                               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Convert incoming percentage value 0 - 100% to an integer in base sixteen 00 - FF (0 - 255). Where 100% = 255 and 1% = 2.55 (Rounding.HALF_UP) accordingly but as two hex digits (e.g. 00, 03, 7F, FF)
        Parameters:
        percentage - 0 - 100%
        Returns:
        Hexadecimal representation from 00 to FF as two hex digits.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a given percentage below 0 or above 100%
